  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">10000 Washable Sanitary Pads for African women</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Limpopo, South Africa, young girls skip school during their menstrual period because they can&apos;t afford hygiene products. We provide washable, reusable pads to these girls so that they can stay in school. Longterm, we will help limit the ecological damage caused by disposable pads being thrown into rivers and on the streets in rural areas where there is no municipal trash collection. This project will also create jobs and seamstress training for local women in our Sewing Project to make pads.</narrative>
  </description>
